<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 14 at 8:22PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Bryan
and south central Atoka Counties through 845 PM CDT...
At 822 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Bokchito, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Caddo, Bokchito, Bennington and Blue.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
